The paper discusses recent advances in Neural Question Generation (NQG), which is a subfield of Natural Language Processing (NLP). The paper examines the corpora, methodologies, and evaluation methods used in NQG, which are all relevant to the sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the learning paradigms, input modalities, and cognitive levels considered by NQG, which are relevant to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Neural Networks (cs.NE), and Information Retrieval (cs.IR).
